<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221871>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Ascoleucetta ventricosa. A – B, Preserved specimen (BMNH 1887.7.12.7 (ii) (modified from Cavalcanti & Klautau 2011; Copyright permission 11035892); C, WAM Z 40336; D – F, SAM S 887. C, Transverse section showing the cortex (ct), choanocyte tubes and atrium (at); D, Cortical skeleton (SEM); E, Microdiactines (arrow) protruding into the lumen of an inhalant aperture (SEM); F, Microdiactines (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221871/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221872>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Ascoleucetta ventricosa (BMNH 1886.12. 15.32, lectotype); A, Apical actine of a tetractine projected into the lumen of a choanocyte tube (arrow); B, Atrial membrane; C, Cortical triactine; D, Choanosomal triactine; E, Tetractine; F, Apical actine of a tetractine (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221872/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

